25|$|The Second Malaysia Plan {{was also}} {{forced to confront}} an {{unexpected}} problem: inflation. Between 1972 and 1975, <b>the</b> <b>consumer</b> <b>price</b> <b>index</b> (CPI) unexpectedly increased by 40%. In 1974, the inflation rate averaged 18%, although it was reduced to 7% by 1975. This new conundrum was therefore considered by the government when it set out the Third Malaysia Plan (1976–1980).|$|E
